690
01:01:27,640 --> 01:01:30,552
Who would ever talk
about ugly. miserable...

691
01:01:30,719 --> 01:01:33,950
...moping Moaning Myrtle?

692
01:01:40,880 --> 01:01:42,916
She's a little sensitive.

693
01:01:47,239 --> 01:01:49,116
Gather round!

694
01:01:49,440 --> 01:01:54,230
Gather round.
Can everybody see me?

695
01:01:54,400 --> 01:01:57,392
Can you all hear me?

696
01:01:58,039 --> 01:01:59,313
Excellent.

697
01:01:59,799 --> 01:02:03,348
In light of the dark events
of recent weeks...

698
01:02:03,520 --> 01:02:07,991
...Professor Dumbledore has granted me
permission to start this Dueling Club...

699
01:02:08,160 --> 01:02:12,631
...to train you all up in case
you ever need to defend yourselves...

700
01:02:12,880 --> 01:02:15,314
...as I myself have done
on countless occasions.

701
01:02:15,520 --> 01:02:19,035
For full details.
see my published works.

702
01:02:23,559 --> 01:02:26,551
Let me introduce my assistant...

703
01:02:26,720 --> 01:02:29,234
...Professor Snape.

704
01:02:32,440 --> 01:02:35,113
He has sportingly agreed to help
with a short demonstration.

705
01:02:35,279 --> 01:02:37,235
I don't want any of you
youngsters to worry.

706
01:02:37,399 --> 01:02:42,109
You'll still have your Potions master
when I'm through with him. Never fear.

707
01:02:57,120 --> 01:02:58,678
One.

708
01:02:58,840 --> 01:02:59,829
Two.

709
01:03:00,599 --> 01:03:03,511
-T hree!
-Exp elliarmus!

710
01:03:11,760 --> 01:03:14,320
-Do you think he's all right?
-Who cares?

711
01:03:14,480 --> 01:03:17,313
An excellent idea to show them that.
Professor Snape...

712
01:03:17,479 --> 01:03:21,836
...but if you don't mind me saying. it was
obvious what you were about to do.

713
01:03:21,999 --> 01:03:25,116
If I had wanted to stop you.
it would have been only too easy.

714
01:03:25,280 --> 01:03:28,590
Perhaps it would be prudent
to first teach the students...

715
01:03:28,759 --> 01:03:33,071
...to block unfriendly spells.
professor.

716
01:03:34,759 --> 01:03:37,068
An excellent suggestion.
Professor Snape.

717
01:03:38,279 --> 01:03:42,352
Let's have a volunteer pair.
Potter. Weasley. how about you?

718
01:03:42,519 --> 01:03:45,875
Weasley's wand causes devastation
with the simplest spells.

719
01:03:46,279 --> 01:03:49,828
