from my own house?

721
01:03:55,120 --> 01:03:57,509
Malfoy. perhaps?

722
01:04:04,720 --> 01:04:07,109
-Good luck. Potter.
-Thank you. sir.

723
01:04:14,759 --> 01:04:16,670
Wands at the ready.

724
01:04:17,239 --> 01:04:20,117
-Scared. Potter?
-You wish.

725
01:04:30,119 --> 01:04:31,757
On the count of three...

726
01:04:31,920 --> 01:04:36,072
...cast your charms to disarm
your opponent. Only to disarm.

727
01:04:36,240 --> 01:04:39,630
We don't want any accidents here.
One.

728
01:04:41,359 --> 01:04:43,793
-Two.
-Everte Sta tum!

729
01:04:54,960 --> 01:04:57,110
Rictusempra!

730
01:05:07,640 --> 01:05:09,358
I said disarm only.

731
01:05:09,520 --> 01:05:11,431
Serpensortia!

732
01:05:19,760 --> 01:05:22,433
Don't move. Potter.
I'll get rid of it for you.

733
01:05:22,600 --> 01:05:27,799
Allow me. Professor Snape.
Alarte Ascendare!

734
01:06:08,599 --> 01:06:11,159
Vipera Evanesca.

735
01:06:17,600 --> 01:06:19,875
What are you playing at?

736
01:06:32,119 --> 01:06:34,713
You're a Parselmouth?
Why didn't you tell us?

737
01:06:34,879 --> 01:06:37,029
-|'m a what?
-You can talk to snakes.

738
01:06:37,199 --> 01:06:42,319
I know. I accidentally set a python
on my cousin Dudley at the zoo once.

739
01:06:42,480 --> 01:06:46,268
Once. But so what?
I bet loads of people here can do it.

740
01:06:46,440 --> 01:06:50,035
No. they can't.
It's not a very common gift. Harry.

741
01:06:50,519 --> 01:06:52,157
This is bad.

742
01:06:52,320 --> 01:06:55,915
What's bad? If I hadn't told
that snake not to attack Justin--

743
01:06:56,080 --> 01:06:59,390
-That's what you said to it.
-You were there. You heard me.

744
01:06:59,559 --> 01:07:03,268
I heard you speaking Parseltongue.
Snake language.

745
01:07:03,440 --> 01:07:06,193
I spoke a different language?

746
01:07:07,239 --> 01:07:09,514
But I didn't realize--

747
01:07:09,680 --> 01:07:12,353
How can I speak a language
without knowing I can?

748
01:07:12,519 --> 01:07:16,353
I don't know. but it sounded like you
were egging the snake on or something.

749
01:07:16,519 --> 01:07:18,157
Harry. listen to me.

750
01:07:18,560 --> 01:07:21,313
There's a reason the symbol
of Slytherin house is a serpent.

751
01:07:21,480 --> 01:07:25,792
Salazar Slytherin was a Parselmouth.
He could talk to snakes too.

752
01:07:26,039 --> 01:07:27,028
Exactly.

753
01:07:27,200 --> 01:07:30,431
Now the whole school's gonna think
you're his great-great-great grandson.

754
01:07:30,599 --> 01:07:32,510
But I'm not.

755
01:07:35,119 --> 01:07:36,996
lcan't be.

756
01:07:38,080 --> 01:07:40,036
He lived a thousand years ago.

757
01:07:40,200 --> 01:07:43,272
For all we know. you could be.

758
01:08:12,160 --> 01:08:14,435
I'll see you back in the common room.

759
01:08:30,160 --> 01:08:34,278
I want blood.

760
01:08:37,040 --> 01:08:41,830
They all must die.

761
01:08:42,399 --> 01:08:44,310
Kill.

762
01:08:44,960 --> 01:08:46,951
Kill.

763
01:08:47,719 --> 01:08:49,914
Kill.

764
01:08:50,240 --> 01:08:54,119
Time to kill.

765
01:09:26,919 --> 01:09:28,750
Caught in the act.

766
01:09:28,920 --> 01:09:30,797
I'll have you out this time. Potter.

767
01:09:31,279 --> 01:09:33,668
Mark my words.

768
01:09:33,840 --> 01:09:37,913
No. Mr. Filch! You don't understand--

769
01:10:03,559 --> 01:10:05,436
Professor...

770
01:10:05,600 --> 01:10:06,919
...I swear I didn't.

771
01:10:07,119 --> 01:10:10,191
This is out of my hands. Potter.

772
01:10:19,440 --> 01:10:22,000
Professor Dumbledore
will be waiting for you.

773
01:10:30,560 --> 01:10:33,028
Sherbet Lemon.

774
01:11:05,600 --> 01:11:07,636
Professor Dumbledore?

775
01:11:23,439 --> 01:11:26,033
Bee in your bonnet. Potter?

776
01:11:28,800 --> 01:11:33,157
l was just wondering
if you put me in the right house.

777
01:11:33,319 --> 01:11:38,552
Yes. You were particularly
difficult to place.

778
01:11:38,720 --> 01:11:42,110
But I stand by what I said last year.

779
01:11:42,280 --> 01:11:45,511
You would have done well in Slytherin.

780
01:11:45,679 --> 01:11:46,953
You're wrong.

781
01:12:15,039 --> 01:12:16,392
Harry?

782
01:12:16,759 --> 01:12:18,909
Professor.

783
01:12:19,079 --> 01:12:22,708
Your bird....
There was nothing I could do.

784
01:12:23,280 --> 01:12:26,477
-He just caught fire.
-And about time too.

785
01:12:27,280 --> 01:12:29,510
He's been looking dreadful for days.

786
01:12:29,680 --> 01:12:31,591
Pity you had to see him
on a burning day.

787
01:12:33,439 --> 01:12:36,556
Fawkes is a phoenix. Harry.

788
01:12:36,720 --> 01:12:39,917
They burst into flame
when it is time for them to die...

789
01:12:40,080 --> 01:12:42,116
...and then they are...

790
01:12:42,280 --> 01:12:45,192
...reborn from the ashes.

791
01:12:53,239 --> 01:12:55,753
Fascinating creatures. phoenixes.

792
01:12:56,199 --> 01:12:59,908
They can carry immensely heavy loads.

793
01:13:00,079 --> 01:13:02,798
Their tears have healing powers.

794
01:13:05,319 --> 01:13:08,231
Professor Dumbledore. sir!
Wait! Listen!

795
01:13:09,200 --> 01:13:11,236
Professor Dumbledore. sir.
it wasn't Harry.

796
01:13:12,360 --> 01:13:15,113
I'd be prepared to swear it
in front of the Ministry of Magic.

797
01:13:16,520 --> 01:13:18,317
Relax.

798
01:13:19,039 --> 01:13:20,916
I do not believe...

799
01:13:21,079 --> 01:13:24,435
-...that Harry attacked anyone.
-Of course you don't.

800
01:13:28,039 --> 01:13:30,507
Right. Well. |'||....

801
01:13:30,680 --> 01:13:33,672
-|'|| just wait outside. then.
-Yes.

802
01:13:37,199 --> 01:13:40,714
-You don't think it was me. professor?
-No. Harry.

803
01:13:40,879 --> 01:13:43,268
I do not think it was you.

804
01:13:44,279 --> 01:13:45,997
But I must ask you...

805
01:13:46,560 --> 01:13:50,473
...is there something
you wish to tell me?

806
01:13:56,679 --> 01:13:58,510
No. sir.

807
01:13:58,679 --> 01:14:00,112
Nothing.

808
01:14:02,999 --> 01:14:05,069
Very well. then.

809
01:14:05,240 --> 01:14:06,958
Off you go.

810
01:14:43,359 --> 01:14:46,749
Everything's set. We just need a bit
of who you're changing into.

811
01:14:46,919 --> 01:14:48,557
Crabbe and Goyle.

812
01:14:48,719 --> 01:14:51,392
We also need to make sure
that the real Crabbe and Goyle...

813
01:14:51,559 --> 01:14:54,631
...can't burst in on us
while we're interrogating Malfoy.

814
01:14:54,959 --> 01:14:57,553
-How?
-|'ve got it all worked out.

815
01:14:57,719 --> 01:15:00,187
I filled these
with a simple Sleeping Draught.

816
01:15:00,359 --> 01:15:02,998
Simple. but powerful.

817
01:15:03,199 --> 01:15:05,269
Now. once they're asleep...

818
01:15:05,440 --> 01:15:08,512
...hide them in the broomstick cupboard
and pull out a few of their hairs...

819
01:15:08,680 --> 01:15:10,477
...and put on their uniforms.

820
01:15:10,639 --> 01:15:13,790
-Whose hair are you ripping out. then?
-|'ve already got mine.

821
01:15:13,959 --> 01:15:16,996
Millicent Bulstrode. Slytherin.

822
01:15:17,160 --> 01:15:19,230
I got this off her robes.

823
01:15:19,399 --> 01:15:21,913
I'm going to go check
on the Polyjuice Potion.

824
01:15:22,079 --> 01:15:24,673
Make sure that Crabbe and Goyle
find these.

825
01:15:36,320 --> 01:15:38,595
Ron. maybe I should do it.

826
01:15:38,759 --> 01:15:40,715
Yeah. Right.

827
01:15:42,840 --> 01:15:44,592
Wingardium l.eviosa.

828
01:15:54,320 --> 01:15:55,878
Cool.

829
01:16:18,079 --> 01:16:19,831
How thick could you get?

830
01:16:20,000 --> 01:16:21,877
Come on. let's get them.

831
01:16:24,439 --> 01:16:28,273
We'll have exactly one hour
before we change back into ourselves.

832
01:16:36,120 --> 01:16:37,997
Add the hairs.

833
01:16:42,360 --> 01:16:44,032
Essence of Crabbe.

834
01:16:44,200 --> 01:16:45,997
Cheers.

835
01:16:54,360 --> 01:16:56,669
I think I'm gonna be sick.

836
01:16:59,479 --> 01:17:01,231
Me too.

837
01:17:44,280 --> 01:17:45,952
Harry?

838
01:17:46,399 --> 01:17:47,878
Ron.

839
01:17:48,599 --> 01:17:50,669
Bloody hell!

840
01:17:51,439 --> 01:17:53,634
We still sound like ourselves.

841
01:17:53,800 --> 01:17:55,472
You need to sound more like Crabbe.

842
01:17:56,600 --> 01:17:58,795
-Bloody hell.
-Exce|lent.

843
01:17:59,119 --> 01:18:01,508
-But where's Hermione?
-|....

844
01:18:01,680 --> 01:18:04,558
ldon't think I'm going.
You go on without me.

845
01:18:04,719 --> 01:18:06,357
Hermione. are you okay?

846
01:18:06,520 --> 01:18:09,239
Just go. You're wasting time.

847
01:18:11,240 --> 01:18:12,832
Come on.

848
01:18:16,200 --> 01:18:19,397
I think the Slytherin common room's
this way.

849
01:18:22,279 --> 01:18:24,634
Excuse me.

850
01:18:26,359 --> 01:18:28,190
What are you doing d--?

851
01:18:28,360 --> 01:18:30,351
I mean. what are you doing down here?

852
01:18:32,199 --> 01:18:34,793
I happen to be a school prefect.

853
01:18:34,960 --> 01:18:39,238
You. on the other hand. have no business
wandering the corridors at night.

854
01:18:39,800 --> 01:18:41,552
What are your names again?

855
01:18:41,719 --> 01:18:45,553
-|'m....
-Crabbe. Goyle. where have you been?

856
01:18:45,719 --> 01:18:48,631
Pigging out in the Great Hall
all this time?

857
01:18:50,080 --> 01:18:52,275
Why are you wearing glasses?

858
01:18:53,080 --> 01:18:55,799
-Reading.
-Reading?

859
01:18:56,920 --> 01:18:59,115
I didn't know you could read.

860
01:19:01,879 --> 01:19:03,870
And what are you doing down here.
Weasley?

861
01:19:04,040 --> 01:19:05,996
Mind your attitude. Malfoy.

862
01:19:14,439 --> 01:19:16,350
Well. sit down.

863
01:19:19,039 --> 01:19:22,714
You'd never know the Weasleys
were pure-bloods. the way they behave.

864
01:19:22,919 --> 01:19:26,594
They're an embarrassment
to the wizarding world. All of them.

865
01:19:27,399 --> 01:19:29,594
What's wrong with you. Crabbe?

866
01:19:31,719 --> 01:19:33,391
Stomachache.

867
01:19:35,319 --> 01:19:39,949
I'm surprised the Daily Prophet
hasn't done a report on all these attacks.

868
01:19:40,119 --> 01:19:42,474
I suppose Dumbledore
is trying to hush it all up.

869
01:19:42,760 --> 01:19:45,035
Father always said Dumbledore
was the worst thing...

870
01:19:45,200 --> 01:19:48,829
-...that ever happened to this place.
-You're wrong!

871
01:19:56,039 --> 01:19:57,154
What?

872
01:19:57,320 --> 01:20:00,835
You think there's someone here
who's worse than Dumbledore?

873
01:20:00,999 --> 01:20:03,308
Well? Do you?

874
01:20:03,839 --> 01:20:05,636
Harry Potter?

875
01:20:11,920 --> 01:20:13,273
Good one. Goyle.

876
01:20:13,439 --> 01:20:14,918
You're absolutely right.

877
01:20:15,559 --> 01:20:17,311
Saint Potter.

878
01:20:18,280 --> 01:20:20,953
And people actually think
that he's the Heir of Slytherin?

879
01:20:24,559 --> 01:20:27,073
But then you must have some idea
who's behind it all.

880
01:20:27,240 --> 01:20:30,755
You know I don't. Goyle.
I told you yesterday.

881
01:20:31,719 --> 01:20:34,108
How many times do l have to tell you?

882
01:20:35,080 --> 01:20:36,832
Is this yours?

883
01:20:41,119 --> 01:20:43,394
But my father did say this:

884
01:20:43,759 --> 01:20:46,557
It's been 50 years
since the Chamber was opened.

885
01:20:46,719 --> 01:20:50,917
He wouldn't tell me who opened it.
Only that they were expelled.

886
01:20:51,200 --> 01:20:55,671
The last time the Chamber of Secrets
was opened. a Mudblood died.

887
01:20:55,839 --> 01:20:59,957
So it's only a matter of time
before one of them is killed this time.

888
01:21:00,520 --> 01:21:02,272
As for me...

889
01:21:02,439 --> 01:21:04,509
...I hope it's Granger.

890
01:21:04,680 --> 01:21:06,796
What's the matter with you two?

891
01:21:06,960 --> 01:21:09,349
You're acting very odd.

892
01:21:09,520 --> 01:21:11,636
It's his stomachache.

893
01:21:11,800 --> 01:21:13,791
Calm down.

894
01:21:17,800 --> 01:21:19,711
Scar.

895
01:21:23,159 --> 01:21:24,512
Hair.

896
01:21:30,440 --> 01:21:32,715
Hey! Where are you going?

897
01:21:35,599 --> 01:21:36,827
That was close.

898
01:21:36,999 --> 01:21:39,308
Hermione. come out.
We've got loads to tell you.

899
01:21:39,480 --> 01:21:41,277
Go away.

900
01:21:41,759 --> 01:21:45,468
Wait till you see. It's awful.

901
01:21:47,359 --> 01:21:49,031
Hermione?

902
01:21:49,200 --> 01:21:50,758
Are you okay?

903
01:21:52,719 --> 01:21:54,437
Do you remember me telling you...

904
01:21:54,600 --> 01:21:57,637
...that the Polyjuice Potion
was only for human transformations?

905
01:21:57,799 --> 01:22:01,758
It was cat hair I plucked off
Millicent Bulstrode's robes.

906
01:22:04,040 --> 01:22:05,519
Look at my face.

907
01:22:06,600 --> 01:22:08,955
Look at your tail.

908
01:22:15,239 --> 01:22:16,638
Have you spoken to Hermione?

909
01:22:16,799 --> 01:22:19,233
She should be out of hospital
in a few days...

910
01:22:19,400 --> 01:22:22,119
...when she stops coughing up fur balls.

911
01:22:26,679 --> 01:22:28,351
What's this?

912
01:22:32,759 --> 01:22:33,794
Yuck!

913
01:22:33,959 --> 01:22:36,632
Looks like Moaning Myrtle's
flooded the bathroom.

914
01:22:52,199 --> 01:22:56,158
-Come to throw something else at me?
-Why would I throw something at you?

915
01:22:56,559 --> 01:23:00,472
Don't ask me. Here I am.
minding my own business...

916
01:23:00,640 --> 01:23:04,110
...and someone thinks it's funny
to throw a book at me.

917
01:23:04,320 --> 01:23:07,073
But it can't hurt if someone
throws something at you.

918
01:23:07,240 --> 01:23:09,549
I mean. it'll just go
right through you.

919
01:23:10,560 --> 01:23:14,758
Sure! Let's all throw books at Myrtle
because she can't feel it.

920
01:23:14,919 --> 01:23:17,433
Ten points
if you get it through her stomach!

921
01:23:17,600 --> 01:23:20,956
Fifty points if it goes through her head!

922
01:23:21,439 --> 01:23:25,671
-But who threw it at you. anyway?
-I don't know. I didn't see them.

923
01:23:25,999 --> 01:23:30,072
l was just sitting in the U-bend.
thinking about death...

924
01:23:30,279 --> 01:23:33,794
...and it fell through the top
of my head.

925
01:24:02,720 --> 01:24:05,109
“Tom Marvolo Riddle.“

926
01:24:33,759 --> 01:24:35,989
My name...

927
01:24:36,159 --> 01:24:38,957
...is Harry...

928
01:24:40,520 --> 01:24:42,556
...Potter.

929
01:24:55,240 --> 01:25:00,189
Do you know anything...

930
01:25:00,999 --> 01:25:07,393
...about the Chamber of Secrets?

931
01:25:17,119 --> 01:25:18,950
Can you...

932
01:25:20,160 --> 01:25:22,355
...tell me?

933
01:26:22,079 --> 01:26:25,355
Excuse me. Could you tell me
what's going on here?

934
01:26:28,680 --> 01:26:30,910
Are you Tom Riddle?

935
01:26:31,079 --> 01:26:32,797
Hello. can you hear me?

936
01:26:52,520 --> 01:26:54,192
Riddle!

937
01:26:54,759 --> 01:26:56,238
Come.

938
01:26:56,399 --> 01:26:58,310
Professor Dumbledore.

939
01:27:00,399 --> 01:27:02,469
Dumbledore?

940
01:27:03,719 --> 01:27:07,075
It is not wise to be wandering around
this late hour. Tom.

941
01:27:07,240 --> 01:27:10,437
Yes. professor. I suppose l....

942
01:27:10,600 --> 01:27:12,670
I had to see for myself
if the rumors were true.

943
01:27:13,240 --> 01:27:16,038
I'm afraid they are. Tom.
They are true.

944
01:27:16,199 --> 01:27:18,918
About the school as well?
ldon't have a home to go to.

945
01:27:19,079 --> 01:27:21,798
They wouldn't really close Hogwarts.
would they. professor?

946
01:27:21,959 --> 01:27:24,393
I understand. Tom. but I'm afraid...

947
01:27:25,160 --> 01:27:27,958
...Headmaster Dippet
may have no choice.

948
01:27:28,119 --> 01:27:32,431
Sir. if it all stopped.
if the person responsible was caught....

949
01:27:34,600 --> 01:27:36,636
Is there something...

950
01:27:37,520 --> 01:27:39,431
...you wish to tell me?

951
01:27:40,600 --> 01:27:43,034
No. sir. Nothing.

952
01:27:49,520 --> 01:27:52,432
Very well. then. Off you go.

953
01:27:52,600 --> 01:27:54,397
Good night. sir.

954
01:28:29,039 --> 01:28:31,837
-Let's get you out of there.
-Evening. Hagrid.

955
01:28:32,159 --> 01:28:36,311
I'm going to have to turn you in. I don't
think you meant it to kill anyone....

956
01:28:36,479 --> 01:28:38,674
You can't. You don't understand.

957
01:28:38,879 --> 01:28:41,871
The dead girl's parents will be here
tomorrow. The least Hogwarts can do...

958
01:28:42,040 --> 01:28:44,838
...is make sure the thing that killed
their daughter is slaughtered.

959
01:28:45,080 --> 01:28:48,072
It wasn't him.
Aragog never killed no one. Never.

960
01:28:48,399 --> 01:28:50,469
Monsters don't make good pets. Hagrid.

961
01:28:50,640 --> 01:28:52,198
-Now. stand aside.
-No!

962
01:28:52,360 --> 01:28:54,237
-Stand aside. Hagrid.
-No!

963
01:28:54,399 --> 01:28:55,957
Cis tem Aperio!

964
01:29:02,640 --> 01:29:04,870
Arania Exumai!

965
01:29:05,720 --> 01:29:07,119
Aragog!

966
01:29:07,280 --> 01:29:08,474
Aragog!

967
01:29:08,999 --> 01:29:10,318
lcan't let you go.

968
01:29:10,840 --> 01:29:13,991
They'll have your wand for this. Hagrid.
You'll be expelled.

969
01:29:16,440 --> 01:29:18,237
Hagrid!

970
01:29:47,039 --> 01:29:50,998
It was Hagrid. Hagrid opened
the Chamber of Secrets 50 years ago.

971
01:29:51,160 --> 01:29:53,993
It can't be Hagrid.
It just can't be.

972
01:29:54,160 --> 01:29:58,073
We don't even know this Tom Riddle.
He sounds like a dirty. rotten snitch.

973
01:29:58,240 --> 01:30:01,596
The monster had killed somebody. Ron.
What would any of us have done?

974
01:30:01,879 --> 01:30:05,667
Look. Hagrid's our friend. Why don't
we just go and ask him about it?

975
01:30:05,879 --> 01:30:08,439
That would be a cheerful visit.
“Hello. Hagrid.

976
01:30:08,600 --> 01:30:12,275
Tell us. have you been setting anything
mad and hairy loose in the castle lately?“

977
01:30:12,440 --> 01:30:15,512
Mad and hairy? You wouldn't be talking
about me. now. would you?

978
01:30:15,800 --> 01:30:16,789
No.

979
01:30:21,119 --> 01:30:22,677
What's that you've got. Hagrid?

980
01:30:23,119 --> 01:30:27,476
lt's Flesh-Eating Slug Repellent.
For the Mandrakes. you know.

981
01:30:27,639 --> 01:30:31,154
Now. according to Professor Sprout.
they've still got a bit of growing to do.

982
01:30:31,319 --> 01:30:34,675
But once their acne's cleared up.
we'll chop them up and stew them...

983
01:30:34,840 --> 01:30:37,991
...and then we'll get those people
down at the hospital un-Petrified.

984
01:30:39,400 --> 01:30:42,153
In the meantime. though. you three...

985
01:30:42,319 --> 01:30:45,356
...had best be looking after yourselves.
All right?

986
01:30:52,919 --> 01:30:54,750
Hello. Neville.

987
01:30:55,800 --> 01:30:58,189
Harry. I don't know who did it.
but you'd better come.

988
01:30:58,559 --> 01:31:00,197
Come on!

989
01:31:21,839 --> 01:31:25,673
It had to be a Gryffindor.
Nobody else knows our password.

990
01:31:25,840 --> 01:31:27,990
Unless it wasn't a student.

991
01:31:28,159 --> 01:31:31,435
Whoever it was. they must have
been looking for something.

992
01:31:31,600 --> 01:31:32,953
And they found it.

993
01:31:33,679 --> 01:31:36,068
Tom Riddle's diary is gone.

994
01:31:37,600 --> 01:31:38,828
All right. listen up.

995
01:31:39,000 --> 01:31:41,798
We play our game.
Hufflepuff doesn't stand a chance.

996
01:31:41,959 --> 01:31:43,756
We're stronger. quicker and smarter.

997
01:31:43,919 --> 01:31:46,797
Not to mention they're dead scared
that Harry will Petrify them...

998
01:31:46,960 --> 01:31:50,316
-...if they fly anywhere near him.
-Well. that too.

999
01:31:51,479 --> 01:31:52,958
Professor McGonagall.

1000
01:31:53,120 --> 01:31:56,032
-This match has been canceled.
-We can't cancel Ouidditch.

1001
01:31:56,200 --> 01:32:00,955
Silence. Wood. You and your teammates
will go to Gryffindor Tower. Now.

1002
01:32:01,120 --> 01:32:03,680
Potter. you and I will find Mr. Weasley.

1003
01:32:04,039 --> 01:32:06,473
There's something
the both of you have to see.

1004
01:32:08,479 --> 01:32:11,915
I warn you.
This could be a wee bit of a shock.

1005
01:32:19,960 --> 01:32:21,109
Hermione!

1006
01:32:21,279 --> 01:32:22,997
She was found near the library...

1007
01:32:24,199 --> 01:32:26,155
...along with this.

1008
01:32:27,559 --> 01:32:30,278
Does it mean anything to either of you?

1009
01:32:30,439 --> 01:32:31,838
No.

1010
01:32:45,479 --> 01:32:47,709
Could I have your attention. please?

1011
01:32:47,879 --> 01:32:53,272
Because of recent events. these new
rules will be put into effect immediately:

1012
01:32:53,599 --> 01:32:58,514
“All students will return to their house
common rooms by 6:00 every evening.

1013
01:32:58,679 --> 01:33:02,592
All students will be escorted
to each lesson by a teacher.

1014
01:33:02,759 --> 01:33:05,637
No exceptions. “

1015
01:33:06,279 --> 01:33:08,235
I should tell you this:

1016
01:33:08,399 --> 01:33:12,358
Unless the culprit
behind these attacks is caught...

1017
01:33:12,880 --> 01:33:15,917
...it is likely the school will be closed.

1018
01:33:26,959 --> 01:33:29,792
We've got to talk to Hagrid. Ron.
lcan't believe it's him...

1019
01:33:29,959 --> 01:33:32,154
...but if he did set the monster loose
last time...

1020
01:33:32,320 --> 01:33:35,357
...he'll know how to get inside
the Chamber of Secrets. That's a start.

1021
01:33:35,519 --> 01:33:36,713
But you heard McGonagall.

1022
01:33:36,880 --> 01:33:40,031
We're not allowed to leave
the tower except for class.

1023
01:33:40,480 --> 01:33:42,835
I think it's time to get
my dad's old cloak out again.

1024
01:33:55,919 --> 01:33:57,557
Who's there?

1025
01:34:01,199 --> 01:34:02,712
Hello?

1026
01:34:03,320 --> 01:34:04,799
Hello?

1027
01:34:05,919 --> 01:34:10,037
-What's that for?
-Nothing. I was expecting....

1028
01:34:10,199 --> 01:34:13,908
It doesn't matter. Come on in.
| just made a pot of tea.

1029
01:34:16,559 --> 01:34:18,754
Hagrid. are you okay?

1030
01:34:18,919 --> 01:34:21,672
I'm fine. I'm all right.

1031
01:34:22,600 --> 01:34:24,238
Did you hear about Hermione?

1032
01:34:24,719 --> 01:34:28,234
Yeah. I heard about that. all right.

1033
01:34:28,559 --> 01:34:32,074
Look. we have to ask you something.

1034
01:34:33,679 --> 01:34:37,035
Do you know who's opened
the Chamber of Secrets?

1035
01:34:39,279 --> 01:34:41,474
What you had to understand
about that is--

1036
01:34:43,079 --> 01:34:44,592
Ouick. under the cloak.

1037
01:34:45,240 --> 01:34:48,198
Don't say a word.
Be quiet. both of you.

1038
01:34:54,360 --> 01:34:57,318
-Professor Dumbledore. sir.
-Good evening. Hagrid.

1039
01:34:57,479 --> 01:34:59,788
I wonder. could we...?

1040
01:34:59,960 --> 01:35:02,349
Of course. Come in. Come in.

1041
01:35:02,520 --> 01:35:03,839
That's Dad's boss.

1042
01:35:04,000 --> 01:35:07,436
Cornelius Fudge. Minister of Magic.

1043
01:35:07,600 --> 01:35:11,798
Bad business. Hagrid. very bad business.
Had to come.

1044
01:35:11,960 --> 01:35:15,077
Three attacks on Muggle-borns.
Things have gone far enough.

1045
01:35:15,240 --> 01:35:18,312
-The Ministry's got to act.
-But I never--

1046
01:35:18,519 --> 01:35:20,237
You know I never. professor.

1047
01:35:20,400 --> 01:35:23,358
I want it understood. Cornelius...

1048
01:35:23,520 --> 01:35:25,272
...that Hagrid...

1049
01:35:25,439 --> 01:35:27,634
...has my full confidence.

1050
01:35:27,799 --> 01:35:31,428
Albus. look.
Hagrid's record is against him.

1051
01:35:31,600 --> 01:35:34,034
-|'ve got to take him.
-Take me?

1052
01:35:34,199 --> 01:35:36,394
Take me where?
Not Azkaban prison.

1053
01:35:36,679 --> 01:35:40,274
I'm afraid we have no choice. Hagrid.

1054
01:35:40,880 --> 01:35:42,711
Already here. Fudge?

1055
01:35:42,879 --> 01:35:44,153
Good.

1056
01:35:45,039 --> 01:35:47,678
What are you doing here?
Get out of my house!

1057
01:35:48,320 --> 01:35:49,799
Believe me...

1058
01:35:50,079 --> 01:35:54,118
...I take absolutely no pleasure
being inside your....

1059
01:35:55,919 --> 01:35:58,035
You call this a house?

1060
01:35:59,079 --> 01:36:00,068
No.

1061
01:36:00,240 --> 01:36:03,949
I simply called up the school
and was told the headmaster was here.

1062
01:36:04,119 --> 01:36:08,032
Well. what exactly is it
that you want with me?

1063
01:36:08,559 --> 01:36:13,110
The other governors and l have decided
it's time for you to step aside.

1064
01:36:14,679 --> 01:36:17,477
This is an order of suspension.

1065
01:36:22,799 --> 01:36:26,030
You'll find all 12 signatures on it.

1066
01:36:29,760 --> 01:36:33,799
I'm afraid we feel
you've rather lost your touch.

1067
01:36:34,479 --> 01:36:36,709
Well. what. with all these attacks...

1068
01:36:36,879 --> 01:36:39,552
...there'll be no
Muggle-borns left at Hogwarts.

1069
01:36:39,719 --> 01:36:44,076
I can only imagine what an awful loss
that would be to the school.

1070
01:36:44,240 --> 01:36:46,356
You can't take
Professor Dumbledore away.

1071
01:36:46,640 --> 01:36:49,074
Take him away and the Muggle-borns
won't stand a chance.

1072
01:36:49,239 --> 01:36:51,594
You mark my words.
there'll be killings next!

1073
01:36:51,759 --> 01:36:53,351
You think so?

1074
01:36:53,520 --> 01:36:55,909
Calm yourself. Hagrid.

1075
01:36:57,200 --> 01:36:59,839
If the governors desire my removal...

1076
01:37:00,000 --> 01:37:03,549
...I will. of course. step aside.

1077
01:37:05,079 --> 01:37:07,229
However...

1078
01:37:07,880 --> 01:37:12,237
...you will find that help
will always be given at Hogwarts...

1079
01:37:12,400 --> 01:37:14,197
...to those who...

1080
01:37:14,360 --> 01:37:16,590
...ask for it.

1081
01:37:23,120 --> 01:37:25,350
Admirable sentiments.

1082
01:37:25,520 --> 01:37:27,272
Shall we?

1083
01:37:38,880 --> 01:37:40,359
Fudge.

1084
01:37:42,000 --> 01:37:43,752
Come. Hagrid.

1085
01:37:44,840 --> 01:37:46,319
Well?

1086
01:37:46,959 --> 01:37:47,994
|f....

1087
01:37:48,400 --> 01:37:50,834
If anybody was looking for some stuff...

1088
01:37:51,000 --> 01:37:55,676
...then all they'd have to do
would be to follow the spiders.

1089
01:37:55,839 --> 01:37:58,307
Yep. That would lead them right.

1090
01:37:58,479 --> 01:38:00,356
That's all l have to say.

1091
01:38:02,000 --> 01:38:05,595
And someone will need
to feed Fang while I'm away.

1092
01:38:08,840 --> 01:38:10,751
Good boy.

1093
01:38:16,640 --> 01:38:18,676
Hagrid's right.

1094
01:38:18,839 --> 01:38:21,672
With Dumbledore gone.
there'll be an attack a day.

1095
01:38:21,839 --> 01:38:23,431
Look.

1096
01:38:29,240 --> 01:38:30,958
Come on.

1097
01:38:34,520 --> 01:38:36,476
Come on. Fang.

1098
01:38:54,000 --> 01:38:55,319
Come on.

1099
01:38:55,479 --> 01:38:56,707
What?

1100
01:38:56,880 --> 01:38:59,997
You heard what Hagrid said.
“Follow the spiders.“

1101
01:39:00,200 --> 01:39:02,714
They're heading to the Dark Forest.

1102
01:39:04,679 --> 01:39:08,957
Why spiders? Why couldn't it be
“follow the butterflies“?

1103
01:39:43,240 --> 01:39:45,879
Harry. I don't like this.

1104
01:39:50,799 --> 01:39:53,871
-Harry. I don't like this at all.
-Shush!

1105
01:40:04,919 --> 01:40:07,353
Can we go back now?

1106
01:40:07,520 --> 01:40:09,192
Come on.

1107
01:40:56,880 --> 01:40:59,519
Who is it?

1108
01:41:00,159 --> 01:41:01,228
Don't panic.

1109
01:41:01,559 --> 01:41:02,992
Hagrid?

1110
01:41:03,400 --> 01:41:04,913
Is that you?

1111
01:41:05,480 --> 01:41:07,311
We're friends of Hagrid's.

1112
01:41:24,679 --> 01:41:27,751
And you?
You're Aragog. aren't you?

1113
01:41:28,359 --> 01:41:29,587
Yes.

1114
01:41:29,760 --> 01:41:33,389
Hagrid has never sent
men into our hollow before.

1115
01:41:33,560 --> 01:41:36,552
He's in trouble. Up at the school.
there have been attacks.

1116
01:41:37,159 --> 01:41:38,911
They think it's Hagrid.

1117
01:41:39,080 --> 01:41:42,550
They think he opened
the Chamber of Secrets. Like before.

1118
01:41:42,759 --> 01:41:44,989
That's a lie.

1119
01:41:45,440 --> 01:41:48,238
Hagrid never opened
the Chamber of Secrets.

1120
01:41:48,839 --> 01:41:51,592
-Then you're not the monster?
-No.

1121
01:41:51,759 --> 01:41:54,671
The monster was born in the castle.

1122
01:41:54,879 --> 01:41:59,953
I came to Hagrid from a distant land
in the pocket of a traveler.

1123
01:42:00,560 --> 01:42:02,118
Harry.

1124
01:42:03,959 --> 01:42:08,350
But if you're not the monster. then
what did kill that girl 50 years ago?

1125
01:42:08,520 --> 01:42:11,398
We do not speak of it.

1126
01:42:11,720 --> 01:42:17,033
It is an ancient creature we
spiders fear above all others.

1127
01:42:17,199 --> 01:42:18,917
But have you seen it?

1128
01:42:19,559 --> 01:42:25,156
I never saw any part of the castle
but the box in which Hagrid kept me.

1129
01:42:25,319 --> 01:42:28,356
The girl was discovered
in a bathroom.

1130
01:42:28,520 --> 01:42:32,832
When I was accused.
Hagrid brought me here.

1131
01:42:33,000 --> 01:42:34,911
-Harry!
-What?

1132
01:42:47,240 --> 01:42:50,118
Well. thank you.

1133
01:42:51,039 --> 01:42:53,109
We'll just go.

1134
01:42:53,559 --> 01:42:55,231
Go?

1135
01:42:55,440 --> 01:42:57,158
I think not.

1136
01:42:57,319 --> 01:43:02,552
My sons and daughters
do not harm Hagrid on my command.

1137
01:43:02,719 --> 01:43:05,028
But I cannot deny them
fresh meat...

1138
01:43:05,199 --> 01:43:09,351
...when it wanders
so willingly into our midst.

1139
01:43:09,520 --> 01:43:13,149
Goodbye. friend of Hagrid.

1140
01:43:13,320 --> 01:43:15,072
Can we panic now?

1141
01:43:25,360 --> 01:43:27,191
Know any spells?

1142
01:43:27,360 --> 01:43:30,397
One. but it's not powerful
enough for all of them.

1143
01:43:30,559 --> 01:43:33,198
Where's Hermione when you need her?

1144
01:43:46,159 --> 01:43:47,387
Let's go!

1145
01:43:52,320 --> 01:43:54,311
Arania Exumai!

1146
01:43:59,400 --> 01:44:00,674
Go!

1147
01:44:17,919 --> 01:44:19,910
Glad we're out of there.

1148
01:44:26,599 --> 01:44:28,829
Arania Exumai!

1149
01:44:34,320 --> 01:44:37,915
-Thanks for that.
-Don't mention it.

1150
01:44:48,400 --> 01:44:50,470
Get us out of here.

1151
01:44:50,959 --> 01:44:52,551
Now!

1152
01:44:54,559 --> 01:44:58,632
Come on!
Come on. move faster!

1153
01:45:01,200 --> 01:45:02,474
Come on! Go!

1154
01:45:19,279 --> 01:45:21,235
Get us in the air.

1155
01:45:22,279 --> 01:45:23,678
The flying gear's jammed!

1156
01:45:27,600 --> 01:45:31,229
-Come on! Pull!
-|'m trying!

1157
01:45:59,359 --> 01:46:02,157
Follow the spiders.
Follow the spiders.

1158
01:46:02,319 --> 01:46:06,471
lf Hagrid ever gets out of Azkaban.
I'll kill him.

1159
01:46:19,919 --> 01:46:22,991
I mean. what was the point
of sending us in there?

1160
01:46:23,159 --> 01:46:27,596
-What have we found out?
-We know one thing.

1161
01:46:27,760 --> 01:46:30,991
Hagrid never opened
the Chamber of Secrets.

1162
01:46:31,200 --> 01:46:33,111
He was innocent.

1163
01:46:47,960 --> 01:46:50,315
Wish you were here. Hermione.

1164
01:46:50,839 --> 01:46:53,034
We need you.

1165
01:46:53,919 --> 01:46:55,910
Now more than ever.

1166
01:47:12,159 --> 01:47:15,435
-What's that?
-Ron. . ..

1167
01:47:16,240 --> 01:47:20,518
This is why Hermione was in
the library the day she was attacked.

1168
01:47:21,039 --> 01:47:22,233
Come on.

1169
01:47:22,879 --> 01:47:25,712
“Of the many fearsome beasts
that roam our land...

1170
01:47:25,879 --> 01:47:30,316
...none is more deadly than the basilisk.
Capable of living for hundreds of years...

1171
01:47:30,480 --> 01:47:34,109
...instant death awaits any who meet
this giant serpent's eye.

1172
01:47:34,280 --> 01:47:37,158
Spiders flee before it.“
Ron. this is it.

1173
01:47:37,320 --> 01:47:39,993
The monster in the Chamber
of Secrets is a basilisk.

1174
01:47:40,159 --> 01:47:43,913
That's why I can hear it speak.
It's a snake.

1175
01:47:44,239 --> 01:47:49,313
But if it kills by looking people
in the eye. why is it no one's dead?

1176
01:47:59,520 --> 01:48:02,318
Because no one did look it
in the eye.

1177
01:48:04,200 --> 01:48:06,668
Not directly. at least.

1178
01:48:07,879 --> 01:48:09,995
Colin saw it through his camera.

1179
01:48:10,159 --> 01:48:14,038
Justin-- Justin must have seen the
basilisk through Nearly Headless Nick.

1180
01:48:14,199 --> 01:48:18,033
Nick got the full blast of it.
But he's a ghost. he couldn't die again.

1181
01:48:18,199 --> 01:48:21,191
And Hermione had the mirror.

1182
01:48:21,359 --> 01:48:24,590
I bet you she was using it to look
around corners in case it came along.

1183
01:48:24,759 --> 01:48:25,987
And Mrs. Norris?

1184
01:48:26,159 --> 01:48:29,515
I'm pretty sure she didn't have
a camera or a mirror. Harry.

1185
01:48:30,999 --> 01:48:32,796
The water.

1186
01:48:33,240 --> 01:48:38,598
There was water on the floor that night.
She only saw the basilisk's reflection.

1187
01:48:44,480 --> 01:48:46,311
“Spiders flee before it.“

1188
01:48:46,480 --> 01:48:50,075
-It all fits.
-How's a basilisk been getting around?

1189
01:48:50,239 --> 01:48:52,958
A dirty. great snake.
Someone would have seen it.

1190
01:48:53,119 --> 01:48:58,557
-Hermione's answered that too.
-Pipes? lt's using the plumbing.

1191
01:48:58,720 --> 01:49:02,793
Remember what Aragog said
about that girl 50 years ago?

1192
01:49:02,959 --> 01:49:07,032
She died in a bathroom?
What if she never left?

1193
01:49:07,680 --> 01:49:08,954
Moaning Myrtle.

1194
01:49:09,879 --> 01:49:13,758
All students are to return
to their house dormitories at once.

1195
01:49:13,919 --> 01:49:17,195
All teachers to the second-floor
corridor immediately.

1196
01:49:21,999 --> 01:49:27,596
As you can see. the Heir of Slytherin
has left another message.

1197
01:49:27,759 --> 01:49:29,875
Our worst fear has been realized.

1198
01:49:30,040 --> 01:49:34,431
A student has been taken by the monster
into the Chamber itself.

1199
01:49:35,440 --> 01:49:40,878
The students must be sent home.
I'm afraid this is the end of Hogwarts.

1200
01:49:43,159 --> 01:49:45,514
So sorry. Dozed off.
What have I missed?

1201
01:49:45,679 --> 01:49:49,831
A girl has been snatched by the monster.
Lockhart. Your moment has come at last.

1202
01:49:49,999 --> 01:49:52,832
-My moment?
-Weren't you saying just last night...

1203
01:49:52,999 --> 01:49:57,356
...that you've known all along where the
entrance to the Chamber of Secrets is?

1204
01:49:58,639 --> 01:50:03,918
That's settled. We'll leave you
to deal with the monster. Gilderoy.

1205
01:50:04,080 --> 01:50:09,029
-Your skills. after all. are legend.
-Very well.

1206
01:50:09,199 --> 01:50:12,271
I'll just be in my office getting....

1207
01:50:13,080 --> 01:50:14,957
Getting ready.

1208
01:50:17,760 --> 01:50:20,832
Who is it that the monster's taken.
Minerva?

1209
01:50:21,000 --> 01:50:22,752
Ginny Weasley.

1210
01:50:33,679 --> 01:50:36,637
“Her skeleton will lie
in the Chamber forever.“

1211
01:50:40,520 --> 01:50:42,238
Ginny.

1212
01:50:44,240 --> 01:50:47,596
Lockhart may be useless. but he's
going to try and get into the Chamber.

1213
01:50:47,759 --> 01:50:50,353
At least we can tell him
what we know.

1214
01:50:51,639 --> 01:50:54,107
Professor. we have some information
for you.

1215
01:50:55,800 --> 01:50:57,677
Are you going somewhere?

1216
01:50:57,839 --> 01:51:00,831
Well. yes. Urgent call. Unavoidable.
Got to go.

1217
01:51:00,999 --> 01:51:04,071
-What about my sister?
-We||....

1218
01:51:04,400 --> 01:51:07,756
As to that. most unfortunate.
No one regrets more than I.

1219
01:51:07,920 --> 01:51:11,754
You're the Defense Against the Dark
Arts teacher. You can't go now.

1220
01:51:11,919 --> 01:51:14,797
I must say. when I took the job.
there was nothing in the description--

1221
01:51:14,959 --> 01:51:16,074
You' re running away?

1222
01:51:16,239 --> 01:51:18,912
-After all you did in your books?
-Books can be misleading.

1223
01:51:19,080 --> 01:51:21,514
-You wrote them.
-My dear boy. use your common sense.

1224
01:51:21,680 --> 01:51:25,912
My books wouldn't have sold as well if
people didn't think I'd done those things.

1225
01:51:26,480 --> 01:51:27,993
You're a fraud.

1226
01:51:28,159 --> 01:51:30,832
You've been taking credit
for what other wizards have done.

1227
01:51:30,999 --> 01:51:32,876
Is there anything you can do?

1228
01:51:33,039 --> 01:51:37,555
Yes. now you mention it.
I'm rather gifted with Memory Charms.

1229
01:51:37,720 --> 01:51:40,109
Otherwise. all those wizards
would have gone blabbing.

1230
01:51:40,280 --> 01:51:43,272
I'd never have sold another book.

1231
01:51:43,440 --> 01:51:48,912
In fact. I'm going to have to do
the same to you.

1232
01:51:49,400 --> 01:51:52,073
Don't even think about it.

1233
01:52:02,480 --> 01:52:03,879
Who's there?

1234
01:52:06,200 --> 01:52:08,156
Hello. Harry.

1235
01:52:09,039 --> 01:52:13,988
-What do you want?
-To ask you how you died.

1236
01:52:16,280 --> 01:52:18,635
It was dreadful.

1237
01:52:18,800 --> 01:52:22,315
It happened right here
in this very cubicle.

1238
01:52:22,480 --> 01:52:26,359
l'd hidden because Olive Hornby
was teasing me about my glasses.

1239
01:52:26,520 --> 01:52:31,230
l was crying. and then
I heard somebody come in.

1240
01:52:31,400 --> 01:52:37,475
-Who was it. Myrtle?
-I don't know. I was distraught!

1241
01:52:38,719 --> 01:52:41,995
But they said something funny.
a kind of made-up language.

1242
01:52:42,159 --> 01:52:48,234
And I realized it was a boy. so I unlocked
the door to tell him to go away and...

1243
01:52:49,360 --> 01:52:53,990
-...I died.
-Just like that? How?

1244
01:52:54,159 --> 01:52:58,471
| just remember seeing a pair
of great. big. yellow eyes...

1245
01:52:58,640 --> 01:53:02,315
...over there by that sink.

1246
01:53:26,399 --> 01:53:28,355
This is it.

1247
01:53:29,199 --> 01:53:33,829
This is it. Ron. I think this is
the entrance to the Chamber of Secrets.

1248
01:53:35,759 --> 01:53:40,389
Say something. Harry.
say something in Parseltongue.

1249
01:54:29,839 --> 01:54:33,752
Excellent. Harry. Good work.
Well. then. I'll just be....

1250
01:54:33,919 --> 01:54:36,069
There's no need for me to stay.

1251
01:54:36,680 --> 01:54:38,477
Yes. there is.

1252
01:54:40,239 --> 01:54:43,197
-You first.
-Now. boys. what good will it do?

1253
01:54:43,360 --> 01:54:44,634
Better you than us.

1254
01:54:45,800 --> 01:54:48,598
But-- Obviously. yes.

1255
01:54:52,720 --> 01:54:55,314
Sure you don't want to test it first?

1256
01:55:01,839 --> 01:55:04,956
It's really quite filthy down here.

1257
01:55:05,399 --> 01:55:09,756
-All right. Let's go.
-Oh. Harry?

1258
01:55:10,159 --> 01:55:14,869
If you die down there.
you're welcome to share my toilet.

1259
01:55:17,320 --> 01:55:19,197
Thanks. Myrtle.

1260
01:55:47,119 --> 01:55:52,068
Now, remember: Any sign of movement.
close your eyes straightaway.

1261
01:55:53,000 --> 01:55:54,592
Go on.

1262
01:55:58,160 --> 01:55:59,434
This way.

1263
01:56:06,159 --> 01:56:11,187
-What's this?
-It looks like a snake.

1264
01:56:11,360 --> 01:56:14,875
-|t's a snakeskin.
-Bloody hell.

1265
01:56:15,040 --> 01:56:20,592
Whatever shed this must be
60 feet long. Or more.

1266
01:56:22,439 --> 01:56:25,272
Heart of a lion. this one.

1267
01:56:28,840 --> 01:56:33,311
The adventure ends here. boys.
But don't fret.

1268
01:56:35,160 --> 01:56:40,393
The world will know our story.
How I was too late to save the girl.

1269
01:56:40,719 --> 01:56:44,075
How you two
tragically lost your minds...

1270
01:56:44,240 --> 01:56:47,118
...at the sight of her mangled body.

1271
01:56:47,919 --> 01:56:49,318
So....

1272
01:56:50,399 --> 01:56:52,629
You first. Mr. Potter.

1273
01:56:52,880 --> 01:56:55,917
Say goodbye to your memories.

1274
01:56:57,879 --> 01:56:59,756
Oblivia te!

1275
01:57:32,280 --> 01:57:35,272
-Ron! Ron. are you okay?
-|'m fine.

1276
01:57:38,879 --> 01:57:40,551
Hello.

1277
01:57:41,200 --> 01:57:42,952
Who are you?

1278
01:57:44,280 --> 01:57:46,840
-Ron Weasley.
-ReaHy?

1279
01:57:47,000 --> 01:57:49,753
And who am |?

1280
01:57:51,439 --> 01:57:55,591
Lockhart's Memory Charm backfired.
He hasn't got a clue who he is.

1281
01:57:55,920 --> 01:58:00,232
It's an odd sort of place. isn't it?

1282
01:58:00,399 --> 01:58:02,435
Do you live here?

1283
01:58:03,119 --> 01:58:05,508
-No.
-ReaHy?

1284
01:58:09,920 --> 01:58:11,638
-What do I do now?
-You wait here...

1285
01:58:11,800 --> 01:58:14,633
...and try and shift some of this rock
so we can get back through.

1286
01:58:14,800 --> 01:58:18,315
-|'|| go on and find Ginny.
-Okay.

1287
01:59:47,719 --> 01:59:51,428
Ginny! Ginny. please don't be dead.
Wake up. wake up.

1288
01:59:51,919 --> 01:59:53,910
Please wake up.

1289
01:59:54,159 --> 01:59:56,229
She won't wake.

1290
02:00:01,479 --> 02:00:05,631
Tom. Tom Riddle.
What do you mean. she won't wake?

1291
02:00:05,800 --> 02:00:09,031
-She's not...?
-She's still alive. but only just.

1292
02:00:10,000 --> 02:00:12,195
-Are you a ghost?
-A memory...

1293
02:00:12,359 --> 02:00:14,634
...preserved in a diary for 50 years.

1294
02:00:17,200 --> 02:00:22,194
She's cold as ice.
Ginny. please don't be dead. Wake up.

1295
02:00:22,359 --> 02:00:24,668
You've got to help me. Tom.
There's a basilisk.

1296
02:00:24,839 --> 02:00:27,307
It won't come until it's called.

1297
02:00:30,000 --> 02:00:32,719
-Give me my wand. Tom.
-You won't be needing it.

1298
02:00:33,720 --> 02:00:36,996
-We've got to go. We've got to save her.
-|'m afraid I can't do that.

1299
02:00:37,159 --> 02:00:41,038
You see. as poor Ginny grows weaker.
I grow stronger.

1300
02:00:42,319 --> 02:00:46,631
Yes. Harry. it was Ginny Weasley
who opened the Chamber of Secrets.

1301
02:00:46,800 --> 02:00:49,030
No. She couldn't. She wouldn't.

1302
02:00:49,200 --> 02:00:52,272
It was Ginny who set the basilisk
on the Mudbloods and Filch's cat...

1303
02:00:52,439 --> 02:00:54,794
...Ginny who wrote the threatening
messages on the walls.

1304
02:00:54,960 --> 02:00:58,111
-But why?
-Because I told her to.

1305
02:00:58,279 --> 02:01:03,034
You'll find I can be very persuasive.
Not that she knew what she was doing.

1306
02:01:03,199 --> 02:01:06,396
She was. shall we say.
in a kind of trance.

1307
02:01:06,919 --> 02:01:09,308
Still. the power of the diary
began to scare her.

1308
02:01:09,479 --> 02:01:11,754
She tried to dispose of it
in the girls' bathroom.

1309
02:01:11,919 --> 02:01:16,071
And then who should find it but you?

1310
02:01:16,240 --> 02:01:19,232
The very person
I was most anxious to meet.

1311
02:01:19,800 --> 02:01:21,791
And why did you want to meet me?

1312
02:01:22,159 --> 02:01:25,390
I knew I had to talk to you.
meet you if I could.

1313
02:01:25,560 --> 02:01:28,711
So I decided to show you my capture
of that brainless oaf Hagrid...

1314
02:01:28,880 --> 02:01:31,917
-...to gain your trust.
-Hagrid's my friend.

1315
02:01:32,800 --> 02:01:37,191
-And you framed him. didn't you?
-It was my word against Hagrid's.

1316
02:01:37,359 --> 02:01:40,510
Only Dumbledore seemed to think
he was innocent.

1317
02:01:40,679 --> 02:01:42,749
I'll bet Dumbledore saw
right through you.

1318
02:01:42,919 --> 02:01:46,229
He certainly kept an annoyingly close
watch on me after that.

1319
02:01:46,399 --> 02:01:49,550
I knew it wouldn't be safe to open the
Chamber again while I was at school...

1320
02:01:49,719 --> 02:01:51,471
...so I decided to leave behind
a diary...

1321
02:01:51,639 --> 02:01:53,675
...preserving my 16-year-old self
in its pages...

1322
02:01:53,839 --> 02:01:56,399
...so that one day
I would be able to lead another...

1323
02:01:56,560 --> 02:01:59,279
...to finish Salazar Slytherin's
noble work.

1324
02:01:59,439 --> 02:02:01,589
Well. you haven't finished it
this time.

1325
02:02:01,759 --> 02:02:04,592
In a few hours. the Mandrake Draught
will be ready.

1326
02:02:04,759 --> 02:02:07,398
And everyone who was Petrified
will be all right again.

1327
02:02:07,759 --> 02:02:12,787
Haven't I told you? Killing Mudbloods
doesn't matter to me anymore.

1328
02:02:13,040 --> 02:02:17,636
For many months now.
my new target has been you.

1329
02:02:19,040 --> 02:02:22,476
How is it that a baby
with no extraordinary magical talent...

1330
02:02:22,639 --> 02:02:25,199
...was able to defeat the greatest wizard
of all time?

1331
02:02:25,519 --> 02:02:28,352
How did you escape with nothing
but a scar...

1332
02:02:28,519 --> 02:02:30,794
...while Lord Voldemort's powers
were destroyed?

1333
02:02:30,960 --> 02:02:34,953
Why do you care how I escaped?
Voldemort was after your time.

1334
02:02:35,119 --> 02:02:41,354
Voldemort is my past.
present and future.

1335
02:03:00,919 --> 02:03:04,229
You. You're the Heir of Slytherin.

1336
02:03:07,279 --> 02:03:10,715
-You're Voldemort.
-Surely you didn't think...

1337
02:03:10,880 --> 02:03:15,192
...l was going to keep
my filthy Muggle father's name?

1338
02:03:15,360 --> 02:03:19,353
No. l fashioned myself a new name.
a name I knew wizards everywhere...

1339
02:03:19,520 --> 02:03:23,559
...would fear to speak when I became
the greatest sorcerer in the world.

1340
02:03:23,719 --> 02:03:26,756
Albus Dumbledore
is the greatest sorcerer in the world.

1341
02:03:26,919 --> 02:03:30,150
Dumbledore's been driven out of
this castle by the mere memory of me.

1342
02:03:30,359 --> 02:03:35,194
He'll never be gone. Not as long as
those who remain are loyal to him.

1343
02:03:41,319 --> 02:03:42,308
Fawkes?

1344
02:03:57,919 --> 02:04:01,355
So this is what Dumbledore
sends his great defender.

1345
02:04:01,520 --> 02:04:05,035
A songbird and an old hat.

1346
02:04:17,799 --> 02:04:22,156
Let's match the power of Lord
Voldemort. Heir of Salazar Slytherin...

1347
02:04:22,319 --> 02:04:26,153
...against the famous Harry Potter.

1348
02:04:38,960 --> 02:04:43,112
Parseltongue won't save you now.
Potter. It only obeys me.

1349
02:05:12,080 --> 02:05:13,559
No!

1350
02:05:14,000 --> 02:05:18,312
Your bird may have blinded the basilisk.
but it can still hear you.

1351
02:06:56,119 --> 02:06:59,270
Yes. Potter.
The process is nearly complete.

1352
02:06:59,439 --> 02:07:04,149
In a few minutes. Ginny Weasley will be
dead. and I will cease to be a memory.

1353
02:07:04,319 --> 02:07:06,879
Lord Voldemort will return...

1354
02:07:07,239 --> 02:07:11,278
...very much alive.

1355
02:07:11,959 --> 02:07:13,312
Ginny?

1356
02:09:24,080 --> 02:09:25,593
Remarkable. isn't it...

1357
02:09:25,760 --> 02:09:29,594
...how quickly the venom
of the basilisk penetrates the body?

1358
02:09:29,760 --> 02:09:32,320
I'd guess you have little more
than a minute to live.

1359
02:09:32,639 --> 02:09:36,518
You'll be with your dear
Mudblood mother soon. Harry.

1360
02:09:41,320 --> 02:09:44,835
Funny. the damage a silly
little book can do...

1361
02:09:44,999 --> 02:09:49,834
...especially in the hands
of a silly little girl.

1362
02:09:52,560 --> 02:09:54,312
What are you doing?

1363
02:09:57,039 --> 02:09:59,075
Stop. No!

1364
02:10:54,960 --> 02:10:58,794
It was me.
But I swear. I didn't mean to.

1365
02:10:58,960 --> 02:11:02,316
Riddle made me. and....

1366
02:11:02,799 --> 02:11:05,359
Harry. you're hurt.

1367
02:11:05,680 --> 02:11:07,113
Don't worry.

1368
02:11:07,280 --> 02:11:10,795
Ginny. you need
to get yourself out.

1369
02:11:10,960 --> 02:11:14,077
Follow the Chamber
and you'll find Ron.

1370
02:11:25,719 --> 02:11:27,755
You were brilliant. Fawkes.

1371
02:11:28,839 --> 02:11:31,148
| just wasn't quick enough.

1372
02:11:51,119 --> 02:11:52,757
Of course.

1373
02:11:53,040 --> 02:11:55,759
Phoenix tears have healing powers.

1374
02:11:57,320 --> 02:11:59,038
Thanks.

1375
02:12:00,719 --> 02:12:02,755
It's all right. Ginny.

1376
02:12:03,840 --> 02:12:05,956
It's over.

1377
02:12:06,920 --> 02:12:09,354
It's just a memory.

1378
02:12:12,119 --> 02:12:17,239
Amazing!
This is just like magic!

1379
02:12:28,079 --> 02:12:30,639
You both realize. of course...

1380
02:12:30,799 --> 02:12:36,078
...that in the past few hours. you have
broken perhaps a dozen school rules.

1381
02:12:36,679 --> 02:12:37,668
Yes. sir.

1382
02:12:37,839 --> 02:12:40,911
There is sufficient evidence
to have you both expelled.

1383
02:12:41,080 --> 02:12:42,229
Yes. sir.

1384
02:12:42,400 --> 02:12:45,039
Therefore. it is only fitting...

1385
02:12:46,519 --> 02:12:48,714
...that you both receive...

1386
02:12:49,200 --> 02:12:53,113
...Special Awards for Services
to the School.

1387
02:12:55,120 --> 02:12:56,872
Thanks. sir.

1388
02:12:57,440 --> 02:12:59,635
Now. Mr. Weasley. if you would...

1389
02:12:59,799 --> 02:13:03,792
...have an owl deliver these
release papers to Azkaban.

1390
02:13:04,880 --> 02:13:09,431
I believe we want
our gamekeeper back.

1391
02:13:14,200 --> 02:13:18,352
First. I want to thank you. Harry.

1392
02:13:18,960 --> 02:13:22,316
You must have shown me
real loyalty down in the Chamber.

1393
02:13:23,160 --> 02:13:27,551
Nothing but that
could have called Fawkes to you.

1394
02:13:29,840 --> 02:13:31,319
And...

1395
02:13:31,879 --> 02:13:33,232
...second...

1396
02:13:33,399 --> 02:13:37,995
...I sense that something
is troubling you.

1397
02:13:38,200 --> 02:13:40,589
Am I right. Harry?

1398
02:13:42,359 --> 02:13:44,031
It's just....

1399
02:13:45,159 --> 02:13:49,675
You see. sir. I couldn't help
but notice certain things. certain....

1400
02:13:49,839 --> 02:13:55,277
Certain similarities
between Tom Riddle and me.

1401
02:13:55,799 --> 02:13:56,948
| see.

1402
02:13:57,120 --> 02:14:02,672
Well. you can speak
Parseltongue. Harry. Why?

1403
02:14:03,120 --> 02:14:08,399
Because Lord Voldemort
can speak Parseltongue.

1404
02:14:09,560 --> 02:14:12,199
If I'm not mistaken. Harry...

1405
02:14:12,559 --> 02:14:16,234
...he transferred
some of his powers to you...

1406
02:14:16,399 --> 02:14:19,232
...the night he gave you that scar.

1407
02:14:19,399 --> 02:14:23,108
Voldemort transferred
some of his powers to me?

1408
02:14:24,960 --> 02:14:27,554
Not intentionally...

1409
02:14:28,399 --> 02:14:30,230
...but yes.

1410
02:14:32,079 --> 02:14:35,276
So the Sorting Hat was right.
I should be in Slytherin.

1411
02:14:35,439 --> 02:14:40,069
It's true. You possess many of the
qualities that Voldemort himself prizes.

1412
02:14:40,239 --> 02:14:42,958
Determination. resourcefulness...

1413
02:14:43,120 --> 02:14:46,954
...and if I may say so.
a certain disregard for the rules.

1414
02:14:47,639 --> 02:14:51,473
Why. then. did the Sorting Hat
place you in Gryffindor?

1415
02:14:52,279 --> 02:14:55,794
-Because I asked it to.
-Exactly. Harry. Exactly.

1416
02:14:55,959 --> 02:14:57,950
Which makes you different
from Voldemort.

1417
02:14:58,119 --> 02:15:01,828
It is not our abilities
that show what we truly are.

1418
02:15:02,119 --> 02:15:04,155
It is our choices.

1419
02:15:07,680 --> 02:15:10,956
If you want proof
why you belong in Gryffindor...

1420
02:15:11,120 --> 02:15:15,796
...then I suggest
you look more closely at this.

1421
02:15:16,760 --> 02:15:18,352
Be careful.

1422
02:15:23,800 --> 02:15:26,360
Godric Gryffindor.

1423
02:15:26,520 --> 02:15:30,433
It would take a true Gryffindor
to pull that out of the hat.

1424
02:15:38,960 --> 02:15:40,279
Dobby.

1425
02:15:41,520 --> 02:15:45,718
So this is your master.
The family you serve is the Malfoys.

1426
02:15:47,799 --> 02:15:50,996
l'll deal with you later.

1427
02:15:56,599 --> 02:15:58,157
Out of my way. Potter.

1428
02:15:58,320 --> 02:16:01,756
So it's true. You have returned.

1429
02:16:02,399 --> 02:16:05,072
When the governors learned that
Arthur Weasley's daughter...

1430
02:16:05,240 --> 02:16:09,233
...was taken into the Chamber.
they saw fit to summon me back.

1431
02:16:10,040 --> 02:16:13,953
-Ridicu|ous.
-Curious|y. Lucius. several of them...

1432
02:16:14,119 --> 02:16:17,634
...were under the impression
that you would curse their family...

1433
02:16:17,799 --> 02:16:20,518
...if they did not agree
to suspend me in the first place.

1434
02:16:20,960 --> 02:16:24,270
-How dare you!
-Beg your pardon?

1435
02:16:24,440 --> 02:16:28,069
My sole concern has always been
and will always be...

1436
02:16:28,240 --> 02:16:30,959
...the welfare of this school...

1437
02:16:31,119 --> 02:16:35,237
...and. of course. its students.

1438
02:16:39,120 --> 02:16:43,159
The culprit has been identified.
I presume?

1439
02:16:43,520 --> 02:16:44,999
Yes.

1440
02:16:46,519 --> 02:16:48,271
And?

1441
02:16:49,399 --> 02:16:51,355
Who was it?

1442
02:16:57,520 --> 02:16:59,954
Voldemort.

1443
02:17:01,079 --> 02:17:06,312
Only this time he chose to act
through somebody else...

1444
02:17:06,839 --> 02:17:10,309
...by means of this.

1445
02:17:12,879 --> 02:17:14,358
| see.

1446
02:17:15,760 --> 02:17:19,799
Fortunately. our young Mr. Potter
discovered it.

1447
02:17:20,119 --> 02:17:23,634
One hopes that no more of Lord
Voldemort's old school-things...

1448
02:17:23,799 --> 02:17:26,916
...should find their way
into innocent hands.

1449
02:17:27,239 --> 02:17:30,993
The consequences for the one
responsible would be...

1450
02:17:31,360 --> 02:17:33,157
. . .severe.

1451
02:17:34,519 --> 02:17:37,192
Well. let us hope...

1452
02:17:37,360 --> 02:17:42,673
...that Mr. Potter will always
be around to save the day.

1453
02:17:43,399 --> 02:17:46,994
Don't worry. I will be.

1454
02:17:55,399 --> 02:17:57,355
Dumbledore.

1455
02:17:58,439 --> 02:18:01,829
Come. Dobby. We're leaving.

1456
02:18:18,400 --> 02:18:22,678
Sir?
I wonder if I could have that?

1457
02:18:28,839 --> 02:18:30,352
Mr. Malfoy.

1458
02:18:30,520 --> 02:18:32,636
Mr. Malfoy!

1459
02:18:33,079 --> 02:18:35,149
l have something of yours.

1460
02:18:36,759 --> 02:18:39,592
Mine? I don't know
what you're talking about.

1461
02:18:39,760 --> 02:18:41,239
I think you do. sir.

1462
02:18:41,399 --> 02:18:44,391
I think you slipped the diary
into Ginny Weasley's cauldron...

1463
02:18:44,560 --> 02:18:45,913
...that day at Diagon Alley.

1464
02:18:46,599 --> 02:18:49,033
You do. do you?

1465
02:18:56,079 --> 02:18:59,037
Why don't you prove it?

1466
02:19:05,040 --> 02:19:07,110
Come. Dobby.

1467
02:19:08,359 --> 02:19:10,315
Open it.

1468
02:19:13,680 --> 02:19:15,159
Dobby.

1469
02:19:15,319 --> 02:19:18,356
Master has given Dobby a sock.

1470
02:19:18,640 --> 02:19:20,631
What? I didn't give--

1471
02:19:20,800 --> 02:19:24,349
Master has presented Dobby
with clothes.

1472
02:19:24,520 --> 02:19:27,432
Dobby is free.

1473
02:19:33,720 --> 02:19:37,315
You lost me my servant!

1474
02:19:44,000 --> 02:19:47,834
You shall not harm Harry Potter.

1475
02:19:59,480 --> 02:20:03,029
Your parents were
meddlesome fools too.

1476
02:20:03,200 --> 02:20:06,237
Mark my words. Potter.
One day soon...

1477
02:20:06,400 --> 02:20:11,394
...you are going to meet
the same sticky end.

1478
02:20:16,880 --> 02:20:22,512
Harry Potter freed Dobby.
How can Dobby ever repay him?

1479
02:20:22,880 --> 02:20:26,953
-Just promise me something.
-Anything. sir.

1480
02:20:28,839 --> 02:20:31,194
Never try to save my life again.

1481
02:20:37,079 --> 02:20:39,957
-We|come back. Sir Nicholas.
-Thank you.

1482
02:20:40,239 --> 02:20:42,514
-Good evening. Sir Nicholas.
-Good evening.

1483
02:20:42,679 --> 02:20:45,477
-Good to see you. Sir Nicholas.
-Thank you.

1484
02:20:46,800 --> 02:20:48,916
Hello.

1485
02:20:50,560 --> 02:20:54,997
-Hermione! Welcome back.
-Thanks. Sir Nicholas.

1486
02:20:58,119 --> 02:21:01,316
Harry. lt's Hermione.

1487
02:21:27,040 --> 02:21:30,589
-We|come back. Hermione.
-|t's good to be back.

1488
02:21:30,759 --> 02:21:33,227
Congratulations.
I can't believe you solved it.

1489
02:21:33,399 --> 02:21:35,549
We had loads of help from you.

1490
02:21:35,719 --> 02:21:38,791
-We couldn't have done it without you.
-Thanks.

1491
02:21:40,559 --> 02:21:43,392
Could I have your attention. please?

1492
02:21:47,399 --> 02:21:49,788
Before we begin the feast...

1493
02:21:49,959 --> 02:21:55,955
...let us have a round of applause
for Professor Sprout. Madam Pomfrey...

1494
02:21:56,119 --> 02:22:00,078
...whose Mandrake juice has been
so successfully administered...

1495
02:22:00,240 --> 02:22:02,800
...to all who had been Petrified.

1496
02:22:12,880 --> 02:22:15,758
Also. in light of the recent events...

1497
02:22:15,919 --> 02:22:17,989
...as a school treat...

1498
02:22:18,160 --> 02:22:21,948
...all exams have been canceled.

1499
02:22:24,519 --> 02:22:26,032
Oh, no.

1500
02:22:42,279 --> 02:22:44,235
Sorry I'm late.

1501
02:22:50,039 --> 02:22:54,271
The owl that delivered my release papers
got all lost and confused.

1502
02:22:54,599 --> 02:22:57,750
Some ruddy bird called Errol.

1503
02:23:12,880 --> 02:23:18,637
And I'd just like to say that if it hadn't
been for you. Harry and Ron...

1504
02:23:18,839 --> 02:23:21,672
...and Hermione. of course...

1505
02:23:22,320 --> 02:23:26,233
...I would still be you-know-where...

1506
02:23:26,399 --> 02:23:29,835
...so I'd just like to say thanks.

1507
02:23:38,839 --> 02:23:41,672
There's no Hogwarts
without you. Hagrid.

